DOCKER and CONTAINER

Create an Instance:

Docker can be installed in two ways:

1) Through cmd yum install docker.
2) Through Docker repo - goto docker install - choose the machine - follow the cmds

After installation: To run Ubuntu Container

GOTO to Docker HUB --> search ubuntu -> click official image and copy the cmd

cmds:

sudo su -
hostnamectl set-hostname docker.example.com
bash
yum install docker
systemctl restart docker
systemctl enable docker
docker info
docker images
docker --help
docker pull ubuntu
docker images ls
docker pull httpd
docker ps -a


